President Obama has announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. 

Ernie DuBester is nominated for Member of the Federal Labor Relations Authority. He has served as a Member of the Authority since 2009 and has previous experience as a Mediator at the National Mediation Board and as a Professor and Chair of the Dispute Resolution Program at George Mason University School of Law.

Carol Waller Pope is nominated for Member of the Federal Labor Relations Authority and will be designated Chair upon appointment. She is currently Chairman of the Authority and has been a member since 2000. Prior to her appointment, she worked in the Office of the General Counsel of the Authority and in the Department of Labor.

Ruth David is appointed as a Member of the National Science Board at the National Science Foundation. She is currently the President and CEO of Analytic Services Inc. and has previously held positions at the Central Intelligence Agency and Sandia National Laboratories.

Maria T. Zuber is appointed as a Member of the National Science Board at the National Science Foundation. She is currently the E.A. Griswold Professor of Geophysics at MIT and is the Principal Investigator of NASA's Gravity Recovery and Interior Laboratory Mission.

Laura Skandera Trombley is appointed as a Member of the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board. She is currently the President of Pitzer College and has previously held positions at Coe College and S.U.N.Y. Potsdam.

President Obama expressed confidence in these individuals and looks forward to working with them in their new roles.